io.hekate.spring.boot.metrics.cloudwatch

Class CloudWatchMetricsPluginConfigurer

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.hekate.spring.boot.metrics.cloudwatch.CloudWatchMetricsPluginConfigurer

  • @Configuration
 @ConditionalOnHekateEnabled
 @ConditionalOnProperty(value="hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.enable",
                       havingValue="true")
public class CloudWatchMetricsPluginConfigurer
extends Object
    Auto-configuration for CloudWatchMetricsConfig.

    Module dependency

    Amazon CloudWatch integration is provided by the 'hekate-metrics-cloudwatch' module and can be imported into the project dependency management system as in the example below:

    • Maven
    • Gradle
    • Ivy
    
 <dependency>
   <groupId>io.hekate</groupId>
   <artifactId>hekate-metrics-cloudwatch</artifactId>
   <version>2.4.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
 </dependency>
 
    
 compile group: 'io.hekate', name: 'hekate-metrics-cloudwatch', version: '2.4.0-SNAPSHOT'
 
    
 <dependency org="io.hekate" name="hekate-metrics-cloudwatch" rev="2.4.0-SNAPSHOT"/>

    Configuration

    This auto-configuration is disabled by default and can be enabled by setting the 'hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.enable' property to true in the application's configuration.

    The following properties can be used to customize the auto-configured CloudWatchMetricsPlugin instance:

    • 'hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.publish-interval'
    • 'hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.namespace'
    • 'hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.region'
    • 'hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.access-key'
    • 'hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.secret-key'
    • 'hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.regex-filters' - list of regular expressions to filter metrics that should be published to CloudWatch
    • 'hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.name-filters' - list of metric names that should be published to CloudWatch
    See Also:
